# 4. Project Planning Phase

## Project Timeline (Milestones)
- Phase 1: Research & Ideation: Defining the scope, objectives, and problem statement.
- Phase 2: Requirement Analysis: Identifying necessary technologies, libraries, and hardware.
- Phase 3: Design & Architecture: Planning the application workflow and MVC structure.
- Phase 4: Development: Data collection, preprocessing, model training, and web integration.
- Phase 5: Testing: Unit testing, integration testing, and performance validation.
- Phase 6: Documentation & Final Demo: Finalizing the reports and preparing for the demonstration.

## Task Breakdown (Resources & Allocation)
- Developer Tasks:
  - Coding the Flask backend logic.
  - Developing HTML/CSS templates.
  - Training and tuning the Machine Learning model.
- Documentation Tasks:
  - Creating project reports and technical documentation.
  - Maintaining README files for each project phase.

## Tools and Environment Management
- Environment: VS Code for coding, Jupyter Notebook for experimentation.
- Workflow: Weekly review of development progress against the defined milestones.
- Collaboration: Version control using Git to track changes and manage project versions.
